race.comment: BLAMEITONTHEBOOGIE (3) was spelled off a spacious debut win on the synthetic and resumed at Launceston with a heavily bet win at CL1 level. He's promising and tumbles in weight at this level. That brings him right into it. Listed placed GEEGEES MISSILE (6) brings a string of wins and did it easily as a firm favourite at Launceston last time. She will use the inside barrier and is feared. NAVAL ANTHEM (2) raced favourite second up but looked a run short. He is still well shy of his best and has the tongue tie on again. He will get every chance from the inside barrier. ESPRIT DIVA (4) is racing well and was beaten just 1.3L at Launceston last time. She's in the mix.
